[[div class="article"]]
[[div class="picture"]]
[[span class="heading2"]]INTERNATIONAL[[/span]]

[[image http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/scp-9506/emigration.jpg]]
[[/div]]
[[div class="words"]]
[[span class="heading"]]INTERNATIONAL[[/span]]

[[span class="coolheading"]]Mass Emigration from Indonesia Continues as Fog Intensifies[[/span]]

[[span class="normalcy"]]INDONESIA — Mass emigration from coastal and low-lying regions of Indonesia continues as fog frequency reaches unsustainable levels. Some areas now experience fog multiple times per week, making normal life impossible. Neighboring countries have begun implementing stricter border controls as the refugee crisis escalates...[[/span]]
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

----

[[div class="article"]]
[[div class="picture"]]
[[span class="heading2"]]BREAKING[[/span]]

[[image http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/scp-9506/alert.jpg]]
[[/div]]
[[div class="words"]]
[[span class="heading"]]BREAKING[[/span]]

[[span class="coolheading"]]Alert System Malfunction Leaves Town With 8 Minutes Warning[[/span]]

[[span class="normalcy"]]CARTERVILLE, IL — Technical failure in the regional alert network delayed fog warnings by over 30 minutes last Thursday, leaving residents with only 8 minutes to evacuate. Local officials report 47 confirmed deaths, with search operations still ongoing...[[/span]]
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

-----

[[div class="article"]]
[[div class="picture"]]
[[span class="heading2"]]FEATURE[[/span]]

[[image http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/scp-9506/Sam.jpg]]
[[/div]]
[[div class="words"]]
[[span class="heading"]]FEATURE[[/span]]

[[span class="coolheading"]]Inside Sam Altman’s Underground Fog Bunker: Safety in Style[[/span]]

[[span class="normalcy"]]SAN FRANCISCO, CA — We were invited to tour Sam Altman’s private underground bunker inside his Russian Hill residence. The bunker is a fully integrated living space designed for comfortable fog survival. It features multiple sealed “quiet rooms” with independent air systems and automated lockdown, along with living areas that convert into safe zones during alerts...[[/span]]
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

-----

[[div class="article"]]
[[div class="picture"]]
[[span class="heading2"]]SCIENCE[[/span]]

[[image http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/scp-9506/earth.jpg]]
[[/div]]
[[div class="words"]]
[[span class="heading"]]SCIENCE[[/span]]

[[span class="coolheading"]]Climate Change Continues to Worsen Global Fog Conditions[[/span]]

[[span class="normalcy"]]GENEVA — Climate scientists warn that rising temperatures and shifting atmospheric patterns are accelerating fog frequency worldwide, a trend documented for over two decades. Melting ice sheets and changing weather systems continue to create more favorable conditions for fog formation, particularly affecting coastal and low-lying regions...[[/span]]
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

-----

[[div class="article"]]
[[div class="picture"]]
[[span class="heading2"]]LOCAL[[/span]]

[[image http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/scp-9506/memorial.jpg]]
[[/div]]
[[div class="words"]]
[[span class="heading"]]LOCAL[[/span]]

[[span class="coolheading"]]Community Dedicates Memorial for Fog Victims[[/span]]

[[span class="normalcy"]]ASHEVILLE, NC — The town of Asheville dedicated a memorial structure this weekend honoring the 183 residents who died during the March 2023 fog. The memorial, located in Riverside Cemetery, features engraved plaques with victims' names. "These were our neighbors, our friends, our family."...[[/span]]
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

-----

[[div class="article"]]
[[div class="picture"]]
[[span class="heading2"]]FEATURE[[/span]]

[[image http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/scp-9506/hunt.jpg]]
[[/div]]
[[div class="words"]]
[[span class="heading"]]FEATURE[[/span]]

[[span class="coolheading"]]The Dangerous Trend of ‘Fog Hunting’[[/span]]

[[span class="normalcy"]]A social media trend known as “fog hunting” has been on the rise. Users seek out active fog and attempt to get as close as possible to the edge. Most posts show users filming the fog line as it moves in, timing how long they can stay nearby before having to leave. The goal is to “beat” their previous distance. The trend has gained traction among younger users across multiple platforms...[[/span]]
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

-----

[[div class="article"]]
[[div class="picture"]]
[[span class="heading2"]]LOCAL[[/span]]

[[image http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/scp-9506/opening.jpg]]
[[/div]]
[[div class="words"]]
[[span class="heading"]]LOCAL[[/span]]

[[span class="coolheading"]]New Training Center Opens in Portland[[/span]]

[[span class="normalcy"]]PORTLAND, OR — A new NFSI training facility opened Monday in Southeast Portland, the fifth such center to open in Oregon this year. The facility will provide free basic protocol training and advanced breathing certification to residents in the Portland metropolitan area. The center can accommodate up to 200 trainees per week and offers evening and weekend sessions for working families...[[/span]]
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

-----

[[div class="article"]]
[[div class="picture"]]
[[span class="heading2"]]BUSINESS[[/span]]

[[image http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/scp-9506/podium.jpg]]
[[/div]]
[[div class="words"]]
[[span class="heading"]]BUSINESS[[/span]]

[[span class="coolheading"]]Calls Grow for Fog Hazard Pay Increase[[/span]]

[[span class="normalcy"]]OAKLAND, CA — Labor groups are calling for an increase to “fog hazard pay” rates in regions regularly affected by fog events, arguing that current compensation does not reflect the risk and disruption. Proposals include higher automatic wage multipliers during active alerts, along with expanded eligibility for partial pay during missed or interrupted shifts...[[/span]]
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

-----

[[div class="article"]]
[[div class="picture"]]
[[span class="heading2"]]EDUCATIONAL[[/span]]

[[image http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/scp-9506/cold.jpg]]
[[/div]]
[[div class="words"]]
[[span class="heading"]]EDUCATIONAL[[/span]]

[[span class="coolheading"]]Winter Fog: What to Know[[/span]]

[[span class="normalcy"]]As winter approaches, fog patterns may shift. Now's a good time to review your winter prep and make sure you're ready for cold-weather fog.[[/span]]
[[/div]]
